What was the Vietnamese public's feelings about 
the war? The general public And by the general

34:16.840 --> 34:21.306
public, I'm talking about maybe 80, 90% of the 
population. And again, I'm talking about people

34:22.107 --> 34:27.273
that were living out in the country. They were 
farmers. They were poor people. They were

34:29.637 --> 34:30.678
uneducated. The only thing that these people knew 
anything about was what they heard on the radio,

34:32.941 --> 34:41.251
and radio was prevalent throughout Vietnam.

34:42.854 --> 34:43.995
The general public did not really care, I'm 
talking about the Vietnamese general public, did

34:44.718 --> 34:54.310
not really care about the controversy or the 
issues of the war. They were concerned about

34:54.371 --> 35:03.763
raising their crops, raising the family, doing 
