35:14.452 --> 35:42.788
uh the north vietnamese in particular and also the 
Vietcong, as they stepped up their propaganda,

35:43.493 --> 36:06.664
then a lot of these people that did not want a part of 
the war listened to the propaganda being

35:43.493 --> 36:06.664
broadcast or published or distributed by the 
North Vietnamese. They became to accept us as the

36:07.245 --> 36:11.931
enemy. We were no longer there in the defense of 
their nation, though we were there in the defense

36:12.451 --> 36:28.349
of a government that was by then in disfavor with 
the general public. Was the Vietnamese's

36:29.831 --> 36:34.536
attitudes about fighting the war different from 
that of the Americans? The Vietnamese's you say

36:39.991 --> 37:04.243
their their feelings the soldier i guess in any 
country is

36:39.991 --> 37:04.243
going to feel that he is doing the right thing 
because he is a professional uh what their private

36:39.991 --> 37:04.243
thoughts may have been i cannot answer that 
however as a professional soldier they were more

37:04.831 --> 37:14.661
or less bound to do whatever their superiors 
command that they do. What about their tactics?

37:16.322 --> 37:19.325
Were they different in fighting this war? The 
Texas were definitely different. The United

37:22.748 --> 37:32.678
States, I think, went over with a concept of 
fighting a war like back in World War I and World War

37:33.130 --> 37:42.661
II, and maybe even Korea, where they were definite 
established battle lines. The military refers to

37:43.242 --> 37:47.747
them as the forward edge of the battle area. In 
Vietnam, there was not any such thing. The enemy

37:51.572 --> 37:55.977
could not be identified because he was not in 
uniform. The enemy did not have established

37:57.719 --> 38:02.985
battle lines They would surface during the night 
or even during the day unexpectedly. They would

38:10.094 --> 38:11.897
conduct a raid. They would retreat. They would 
become members of the general public during the

38:16.122 --> 38:20.507
day. That was one of the major reasons,

38:20.527 --> 38:31.841
I guess you might say, why we were not successful in 
Vietnam. We did not know who the enemy was. There

38:34.268 --> 38:42.680
were times when the enemy was found and attacked, 
or there were times when the enemy would attack.

38:43.161 --> 38:50.632
Battles would last for anywhere between a week at 
the very most to 15 days. The

38:51.613 --> 39:03.010
enemy would then dissolve, it seemed like, into 
almost nothing, or he would retreat to what at that

38:51.613 --> 39:03.010
time were considered sanctuaries. We refer to 
this as guerrilla warfare, where you strike and

39:03.648 --> 39:15.526
you retreat, where you make a stand for a few days 
and then disappear. We were not prepared

39:16.568 --> 39:26.263
for this type of insurgency type of warfare. We 
were prepared and we had the firepower to fight a

39:26.944 --> 39:31.731
conventional war. Guerrilla warfare is 
definitely not a conventional type of fighting,

39:33.280 --> 39:39.994
and we were not prepared for it. How was the 
military back in the States after seeing that the

39:41.116 --> 39:48.592
Vietnamese were fighting a guerrilla war? How did 
they change their... Their concept of fighting

39:54.222 --> 39:59.149
did not change. The United States wanted to 
continue with a conventional type of warfare.

